trans-unit.source: Standard allocator methods per the semantics defined above. The deallocate and reallocate methods are @system because they may move memory around, leaving dangling pointers in user code.

trans-unit.source: Standard allocator methods per the semantics defined above. The deallocate and reallocate methods are @system because they may move memory around, leaving dangling pointers in user code. Somewhat paradoxically, malloc is @safe but that's only useful to safe programs that can afford to leak memory allocated.
trans-unit.target: 按照上面定义的语义的标准分配器方法。该 deallocate 和 reallocate 的方法是 @system ，因为它们可能会移动存储身边，留下悬摆指针的用户代码。有点自相矛盾的是， malloc 是 @safe ,但是它仅对能够负担泄漏分配的内存的安全程序有用。

trans-unit.source: Standard allocator methods. Each is defined if and only if the parent allocator defines the homonym method (except for goodAllocSize, which may use the global default). Also, the methods will be shared if the parent allocator defines them as such.
trans-unit.target: 标准分配器方法。仅当父分配器定义了同音异义方法时才定义每个方法（ goodAllocSize 除外，后者可能使用全局默认值）。同样，如果父分配器按原样定义方法，则将 shared 这些方法。

trans-unit.source: Static arrays are value types. They are passed to and returned by functions by value.
trans-unit.target: 静态数组是值类型。它们通过值传递给函数并由函数返回。

trans-unit.source: Static arrays have a length fixed at compile time.
trans-unit.target: 静态数组在编译时有一个固定的长度。

trans-unit.source: Static arrays of characters (like char[80]) are not considered built-in string types.
trans-unit.target: 静态字符数组（例如 char[80] ）不被视为内置字符串类型。

trans-unit.source: Static arrays with 0 elements are useful as the last member of a variable length struct, or as the degenerate case of a template expansion.
trans-unit.target: 0元素的静态数组作为可变长度结构的最后一个成员,或者作为模板扩展的退化情况,非常有用。

trans-unit.source: Static constructors and static destructors
trans-unit.target: 静态构造函数和静态破坏函数。

trans-unit.source: Static constructors are executed to initialize a module's state. Static destructors terminate a module's state.
trans-unit.target: 静态构造函数用来初始化一个模块的状态,静态破坏函数用来终止一个模块的状态。静态破坏函数终止模块的状态。

trans-unit.source: Static constructors are used to initialize static class members with values that cannot be computed at compile time.
trans-unit.target: 静态构造函数用于初始化静态类成员,其值在编译时无法计算。

trans-unit.source: Static constructors have empty parameter lists.
trans-unit.target: 静态构造函数的参数列表为空。

trans-unit.source: Static constructors within a module are executed in the lexical order in which they appear. All the static constructors for modules that are directly or indirectly imported are executed before the static constructors for the importer.
trans-unit.target: 一个模块中的静态构造函数是按照它们出现的词法顺序执行的,所有直接或间接导入的模块的静态构造函数都在导入者的静态构造函数之前执行。所有直接或间接导入的模块的静态构造函数都在导入者的静态构造函数之前执行。

trans-unit.source: Static data has one instance per thread, not one per object.
trans-unit.target: 静态数据每个线程有一个实例,而不是每个对象有一个实例。

trans-unit.source: Static functions are never virtual.
trans-unit.target: 静态函数从来不是虚拟的。

trans-unit.source: Static functions with Objective-C linkage are overridable.
trans-unit.target: 具有 Objective-C 链接的静态函数是可重写的。

trans-unit.source: Static initalizations are supplied by a list of array element values enclosed in [ ]. The values can be optionally preceded by an index and a :. If an index is not supplied, it is set to the previous index plus 1, or 0 if it is the first value.
trans-unit.target: 静态初始化由一个用[]括起来的数组元素值列表提供。这些值可以选择在前面加上一个索引和一个:。如果没有提供索引,则设置为前一个索引加1,如果是第一个值,则设置为0。

trans-unit.source: Static member functions with the Objective-C linkage are placed in the hidden nested metaclass as non-static member functions.
trans-unit.target: 与Objective-C链接的静态成员函数作为非静态成员函数放在隐藏嵌套的元类中。

trans-unit.source: Static nested functions cannot access any stack variables of any lexically enclosing function, but can access static variables. This is analogous to how static member functions behave.
trans-unit.target: 静态嵌套函数不能访问任何词义包围函数的任何堆栈变量,但可以访问静态变量。这与静态成员函数的行为类似。
